        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the center side skirt panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure and mark a position for a new bracket at the mid point between two existing
                    brackets on the bottom rail. Repeat the procedure for the second reinforcement bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9990901">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9990901" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g9990901.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position two new brackets, Part Number 3522987C1, at the locations identified in Step 2.
                    Use a C-clamp or other suitable device to hold the new brackets in position on the bottom rail.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the aid of a tight string between existing brackets, insure that the bottom edges
                    of the new brackets are in line with the existing brackets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use the holes in the new brackets as a template and drill 3/16 inch diameter holes in
                    the bottom channel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use two steel rivets, Part Number 2040955C1 or equivalent, to attach each new bracket to
                    the bottom channel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9990901">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the skirt center panel and hand tighten the mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not reuse the fasteners when re-installing the panel. Use the fasteners provided in kit
                        Part Number 8000795R91.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use the two new brackets as a template and drill a 3/8 inch diameter hole at each
                    location. Drill the hole from the backside of the panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the panel with new 5/16-18 bolts, Part Number 3528665C1, and speed nuts, Part
                    Number 3528663C1 (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9990902">Figure 2</hotlnk>). Tighten all panel fasteners to 17 Ft-lbs of torque.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat the procedure to the skirt on the other side.</para>
            </step1>
